Index out of range error when Datamuse provides no results
issue.body:
When Datamuse functions provide no results, Vim takes in an empty list, and then attempts to index it, causing an error:
```
Error detected while processing function muse#DatamuseInterface[5]..muse#ListWords:
line    6:
E684: list index out of range: 0
E15: Invalid expression: a:newwords[nr2char(getchar())]
```

issue.title: Replace python-datamuse submodule with PyPI package
issue.body: This depends on https://github.com/margaret/python-datamuse/issues/4 and will simplify [vim-muse/lib/datamuse_interface.py](https://github.com/gmarmstrong/vim-muse/blob/c19496a77206b12fbfdc30a9bcb5da37ac2c9d52/lib/datamuse_interface.py) by removing [the 5-line "import" of datamuse.py](https://github.com/gmarmstrong/vim-muse/blob/c19496a77206b12fbfdc30a9bcb5da37ac2c9d52/lib/datamuse_interface.py#L8-L13). See [Packaging and Distributing Projects](https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/distributing-packages/) for instructions.
